<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EA7FF2A48A7509DFB99FC37" lastPageId="234" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="233" pageNumber="234" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EA7FF2A48A7509DFA9AFE04" blockId="233.[151,1436,1969,2030]" lastBlockId="234.[151,1438,151,1436]" lastPageId="234" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA7FF2948A7509DFE06F839" bold="true" box="[151,419,1969,1994]" pageId="233" pageNumber="234">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Fully winged; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA7FF294A92509DFC89F839" box="[674,812,1969,1993]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="3.2" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="233" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.7" valueMax="3.2" valueMin="2.2">2.2–3.2 mm</quantity>
. Head brown-reddish or reddish; antenna yellow, except segments 9–10 or only 10 brown; mesosoma, metasoma and legs brown-reddish (occasionally reddish). Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 14:6:8:8:7.5:7:7:7:6:8. Head shiny, smooth, finely punctate, occasionally with transverse keels on face; occipital carina complete; OL not much longer than POL; mandible quadridentate, with one rudimentary tooth between two posterior teeth. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, finely punctate, unsculptured among punctures (in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18EA4FF2A4BD15628FB8BFEEC" box="[993,1070,260,284]" name="Brunei" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Brunei</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4C0B5628FB30FEEC" box="[1083,1173,260,284]" degrees="04" direction="north" minutes="34" orientation="latitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="4.5666666">04°34'N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4CAF5628FAA3FEEC" box="[1183,1286,260,284]" degrees="115" direction="east" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="115.11667">115°07'E</geoCoordinate>
, scutum with anterior half of median region rugose). Notauli complete, posteriorly separated. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with two lateral pointed apophyses; posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels. Fore wing with two dark transverse bands (in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18EA4FF2A4A155643FDD7FE77" box="[549,626,367,391]" name="Brunei" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Brunei</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4A4E5643FD7DFE77" box="[638,728,367,391]" degrees="04" direction="north" minutes="34" orientation="latitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="4.5666666">04°34'N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4AD05643FCE2FE77" box="[736,839,367,391]" degrees="115" direction="east" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="115.11667">115°07'E</geoCoordinate>
, fore wing with one only dark transverse band located beneath pterostigma); stigmal vein strongly curved (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA4FF2A4AE156B8FC99FE5C" box="[721,828,404,428]" captionStart="PLATE 66" captionStartId="227.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[185,1396,226,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-73@227.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="227" captionText="PLATE 66. A. Male genitalia, holotype. B, C. Female stigmal veins. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Bocchus levis (from Olmi 1991). B, D. B. muluensis (from Olmi 1984). C, E. B. pedunculatus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.41 mm for B and C, 0.13 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278607/files/figure.png" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Plate 66C</figureCitation>
); pterostigma short and narrow. Protarsal segments 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA4FF2A4D4356B8FF09FE3F" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 in</quantity>
following proportions: 13:3:3:11. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA4FF2A4AE2569BFC99FE3F" box="[722,828,439,463]" captionStart="PLATE 66" captionStartId="227.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[185,1396,226,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-73@227.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="227" captionText="PLATE 66. A. Male genitalia, holotype. B, C. Female stigmal veins. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Bocchus levis (from Olmi 1991). B, D. B. muluensis (from Olmi 1984). C, E. B. pedunculatus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.41 mm for B and C, 0.13 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278607/files/figure.png" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Plate 66E</figureCitation>
) with one tooth and one bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA4FF2A489056F0FEACFE04" box="[160,265,476,500]" captionStart="PLATE 66" captionStartId="227.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[185,1396,226,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-73@227.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="227" captionText="PLATE 66. A. Male genitalia, holotype. B, C. Female stigmal veins. D, E. Chelae, holotypes. A. Bocchus levis (from Olmi 1991). B, D. B. muluensis (from Olmi 1984). C, E. B. pedunculatus (from Olmi 1984). Scale bar 0.19 mm for A, 0.41 mm for B and C, 0.13 mm for D and 0.16 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278607" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278607/files/figure.png" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Plate 66E</figureCitation>
) with one preapical lamella, two bristles and one distinct proximal prominence. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EA4FF2A48F756D3FB99FC37" blockId="234.[151,1438,151,1436]" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA4FF2A48F756D3FE1DFDE8" bold="true" box="[199,440,511,536]" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Description of male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA4FF2A49FD56D3FDC3FDE7" box="[461,614,511,535]" captionStart="PLATE 67" captionStartId="228.[151,233,1917,1940]" captionTargetBox="[197,1403,201,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-82@228.[151,1436,193,1896]" captionTargetPageId="228" captionText="PLATE 67. A–C. Bocchus pedunculatus. D. B. reticulates. A. Dorsal view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. B. Lateral view of male from Sarawak (from Olmi 1984). Length 2.7 mm. C. Male genitalia of male from Malaysia. D. Holotype (from Xu et al. 2003). Scale bar 0.27 mm for C and 0.23 mm for D." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278609" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278609/files/figure.png" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Plate 67A, B</figureCitation>
): fully winged; length 2.6–3.0 mm. Head black, except mandible and occasionally also clypeus testaceous; occasionally head brown, or reddish-dark; antenna yellow, except segments 6–10 brown (in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18EA4FF2A4A22556BFDC4FDAF" box="[530,609,583,607]" name="Brunei" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Brunei</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4A41556BFD68FDAF" box="[625,717,583,607]" degrees="04" direction="north" minutes="34" orientation="latitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="4.5666666">04°34'N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4AE9556BFCE7FDAF" box="[729,834,583,607]" degrees="115" direction="east" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="115.11667">115°07'E</geoCoordinate>
, antenna totally testaceous); mesosoma and petiole black, or brown, or brown-reddish (in specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="78DE46D18EA4FF2A4ADF5540FC9BFD74" box="[751,830,620,644]" name="Brunei" pageId="234" pageNumber="235">Brunei</collectingCountry>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4B795540FC03FD74" box="[841,934,620,644]" degrees="04" direction="north" minutes="34" orientation="latitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="4.5666666">04°34'N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="65FD60868EA4FF2A4B9C5540FBB0FD74" box="[940,1045,620,644]" degrees="115" direction="east" minutes="07" orientation="longitude" pageId="234" pageNumber="235" precision="925" value="115.11667">115°07'E</geoCoordinate>
, petiole yellow, except ventral side brown); metasoma brown or brown-testaceous; legs testaceous, except coxae blackish. Antenna filiform; antennal segments in following proportions: 17:10:15:14:13:12:11:11:10:15. Head hairy, dull, completely reticulate rugose, occasionally partly granulated; occipital carina complete; ocellar triangle equilateral; OOL = OPL; mandible quadridentate, with one rudimentary tooth between two posterior teeth. Scutum hairy, dull, completely reticulate rugose. Notauli complete, posteriorly separated; minimum distance between notauli longer than POL (7:6). Scutellum and metanotum hairy, dull, finely punctate. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with two lateral pointed apophyses (as in female); posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels. Fore wing with two dark transverse bands; stigmal vein strongly curved; pterostigma short, narrow, lanceolate, hyaline. Petiole very long, approximately 0.25 as long as metasoma. Genitalia in plate 67C. Tibial spurs 1/1/2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
